}
  MDUMP address [length] [/A]

Low Memory

This external command displays memory
contents as hexadecimal and ATASCII
listing. With the A option, non-
printable characters are converted to
printable ones - use this when
printing the listing (see the PRINT
command).

With a length value, only that number
of bytes is shown. Both address and
length must be specified as
hexadecimal numbers.

Press <CONTROL>+<1> to pause or resume
the listing, or press <ESC> to stop
the command.
